## **3. Formalizing the Monomyth as a State Machine**

The monomyth can be represented as the following **transition graph**:

[
S_0 \rightarrow S_1 \rightarrow S_2 \rightarrow S_3 \rightarrow S_4 \rightarrow S_5 \rightarrow S_f
]

Where:

* (S_0): Ordinary World (baseline state)
* (S_1): Call to Adventure (perturbation)
* (S_2): Threshold Crossing (entering uncertainty)
* (S_3): Ordeal / Zero-State (collapse of previous identity)
* (S_4): Transformation (new attractor selection)
* (S_5): Return Integration
* (S_f): Stabilized StateVector (reborn state)

We define the **Zero-State** as:

[
S_3 = \arg\min_{\forall S} ||Identity(S)||
]

Which aligns with Pantheon’s own:

* zero-point state
* apoptosis boundary
* Hogge Zero attractor phase

The transformation is therefore expressed as:

[
S_4 = f(S_3, \text{Attractor Vector})
]

The **Attractor Vector** guides the direction of the new stable state.

