## **5. Mathematical Model of the Transformation Curve**

We define the **primitive of motion** as:

[
M(t) =
\begin{cases}
\text{Stable} & t < t_c \
\text{Collapse} & t = t_c \
\text{Rebuild}(A) & t > t_c
\end{cases}
]

Where (t_c) is the zero-state transition point and (A) is the attractor vector.

The transformation curve is a **piecewise function** representing:

* stability
* discontinuity
* re-convergence
* stabilization

This curve is the structural essence of the monomyth.

